.\" rdpdo - RDP automation tool
.\" Generated from help.rs command documentation
.TH RDPDO 1 "June 2026" "rdpdo 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rdpdo \- headless RDP automation and visual testing tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rdpdo
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.IR COMMANDS ...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rdpdo
connects to an RDP server and executes a chain of automation commands:
keyboard input, mouse actions, visual matching, clipboard operations,
audio capture, and more. Commands are chained on the command line after
global flags.
.PP
Designed for CI/CD visual testing, OS installer automation, golden image
validation, and desktop QA over RDP connections.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-s " HOST" "\fR,\fP \-\-server " HOST
Server address (host or host:port, default port 3389).
Not required for offline commands (diff, convert, audio-verify, help).
.TP
.BI \-u " USER" "\fR,\fP \-\-user " USER
RDP username.
.TP
.BI \-p " PASS" "\fR,\fP \-\-password " PASS
RDP password.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-nla
Disable NLA/CredSSP; use TLS-only authentication.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-auth
Skip authentication entirely (for servers running with \-\-no-auth).
.TP
.BI \-\-timeout " SECONDS"
Overall session timeout (default: 30).
.TP
.BI \-\-width " PIXELS"
Desktop width (default: 1920).
.TP
.BI \-\-height " PIXELS"
Desktop height (default: 1080).
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Enable debug tracing to stderr.
.TP
.BI \-\-record " PATH"
Record all commands with timing to a .rdpdo file for later replay.
.TP
.BI \-\-calibration " PATH"
Apply calibration correction to coordinates.
Use a JSON file path or "auto" to search ~/.config/rdpdo/calibration/.
.TP
.B \-\-json
Emit machine-readable JSON output for matching, stability, pixel,
and measurement commands.
.TP
.BI \-\-fail\-capture " DIR"
Save a diagnostic PNG screenshot on command failure. Writes to the
given directory as fail-NNN.png.
.TP
.BI \-\-junit " PATH"
Write a JUnit XML test report after the command chain completes.
Each command becomes a testcase with timing and pass/fail status.
.SH COMMANDS
Commands are positional arguments chained after options. Multiple
commands execute sequentially in a single RDP session:
.PP
.RS
rdpdo -s host type "hello" key enter pause 2 capture /tmp/out.png
.RE
.SS Input
.TP
.BI type " TEXT"
Type ASCII text via US-QWERTY scancode sequences with 30ms inter-key delay.
.TP
.BI utype " TEXT"
Type text using Unicode keyboard events (any language, any layout).
.TP
.BI key " SPEC" " [--hold-ms MS]"
Send a key or key combination. Names: enter, tab, escape, backspace,
ctrl-alt-delete, f1-f12, etc. Hex scancodes also accepted (0x1C).
.TP
.BI keydown " KEY"
Press and hold a key until a matching keyup.
.TP
.BI keyup " KEY"
Release a previously held key.
.TP
.BI move " POSITION"
Move mouse cursor to a position.
.TP
.BI click " POSITION" " [BUTTON]"
Click at a position. Button: left (default), right, middle.
.TP
.BI doubleclick " POSITION"
Double-click at a position.
.TP
.BI drag " FROM" " TO"
Drag from one position to another.
.TP
.BI scroll " DIRECTION" " NOTCHES"
Scroll up or down by N notches.
.TP
.BI type\-password " SOURCE"
Type a password without logging it. Source: env:VAR, file:PATH, or literal.
.TP
.B mouse\-hide
Move cursor off-screen (65535,65535) to prevent screenshot interference.
.SS Capture
.TP
.BI capture " PATH" " [REGION]"
Save a screenshot to PATH. Use "-" for stdout. Optional region: x,y,WxH.
.TP
.BI rcapture " REGION" " PATH"
Capture a specific screen region.
.TP
.BI timelapse " TEMPLATE" " [FLAGS]"
Periodic screenshot capture. Template uses {n} for sequence number.
Flags: --interval MS, --count N, --duration S, --until IMAGE, --tolerance N.
.SS Visual Matching
.TP
.BI expect " REFERENCE" " [TOLERANCE] [TIMEOUT] [--needles DIR] [--tag NAME]"
Wait until full screen matches a reference image (Pearson correlation).
.TP
.BI waitfor " TEMPLATE" " [TOLERANCE] [TIMEOUT] [--needles DIR] [--tag NAME]"
Search for a template image anywhere on screen and wait until found.
.TP
.BI expectclick " TEMPLATE" " [TOLERANCE] [TIMEOUT] [--needles DIR] [--tag NAME]"
Find a template image on screen, then click its center.
.TP
.BI rexpect " REGION" " REFERENCE" " [TOLERANCE] [TIMEOUT]"
Wait for a screen region to match a reference image.
.TP
.BI repeat\-key " KEY" " TEMPLATE" " [TOLERANCE] [TIMEOUT] [INTERVAL] [MAX]"
Press a key repeatedly until a template matches on screen.
.TP
.BI measure " TEMPLATE" " [TOLERANCE] [TIMEOUT] [--label NAME]"
Time how long until a visual match succeeds. Reports elapsed_ms.
With --json, output is {"label":"...","elapsed_ms":N,"matched":true}.
.TP
.BI diff " IMAGE_A" " IMAGE_B" " [THRESHOLD] [--output PATH] [--mode MODE] [--exclude REGION]"
Offline comparison of two images. Modes: highlight, side-by-side, heatmap.
Exclude regions mask out areas (clocks, timestamps) from comparison.
Does not require an RDP connection.
.SS Screen Stability
.TP
.BI wait\-still " [STILLNESS_MS] [TIMEOUT_S]"
Wait until screen stops updating for the given stillness period.
Default: 500ms stillness, 10s timeout.
.TP
.BI wait\-change " [TIMEOUT_S]"
Wait until the screen changes (a new frame arrives). Default: 30s timeout.
.SS Clipboard
.TP
.BI set\-clipboard " TEXT"
Set clipboard text on the remote server.
.TP
.B get\-clipboard
Read clipboard text from the server (prints to stdout).
.TP
.BI clipboard\-send\-file " PATH"
Send a local file to the remote clipboard.
.TP
.BI clipboard\-recv\-file " PATH"
Receive a file from the remote clipboard and save locally.
.SS Display Control
.TP
.BI resize " WIDTHxHEIGHT"
Resize the remote desktop via DisplayControl channel.
.TP
.BI monitor " ACTION"
Multi-monitor control. Actions: list, set WIDTHxHEIGHT.
.SS Audio
.TP
.BI audio\-capture " PATH" " [DURATION]"
Record audio from the RDPSND channel to a WAV file.
.TP
.BI audio\-assert\-playing " [TIMEOUT]"
Assert that audio is currently playing (non-silence).
.TP
.BI audio\-verify " CAPTURED" " REFERENCE" " [TOLERANCE]"
Offline comparison of two WAV files via Pearson correlation.
Does not require an RDP connection.
.SS Pixel Analysis
.TP
.BI pixel " POSITION"
Read the color of a pixel (prints R,G,B,A or JSON with --json).
.TP
.BI assert\-pixel " POSITION" " COLOR" " [TOLERANCE]"
Assert pixel matches expected color (fail if not).
Color: #RRGGBB or R,G,B. Tolerance: per-channel 0-255 (default: 30).
.TP
.BI wait\-pixel " POSITION" " COLOR" " [TOLERANCE] [TIMEOUT]"
Wait until pixel at position matches a color.
Polls every 250ms. Default: tolerance 30, timeout 30s.
.TP
.BI checksum " REGION"
CRC32 checksum of a screen region's pixel data.
.TP
.BI wait\-checksum\-change " REGION" " [TIMEOUT]"
Wait until a region's checksum changes.
.TP
.BI assert\-checksum " REGION" " EXPECTED"
Assert a region matches a known checksum.
.TP
.BI find\-color " COLOR" " [REGION] [TOLERANCE] [MIN_AREA]"
Find clusters of a color on screen. Reports centroid and bounding box.
.SS Provisioning
.TP
.BI accept\-portal " COMPOSITOR" " [--profile NAME] [--verify]"
Accept a compositor's screen-sharing permission dialog.
.TP
.BI unlock " COMPOSITOR" " PASSWORD" " [--profile NAME] [--verify]"
Unlock a locked screen.
.TP
.BI login " USERNAME" " PASSWORD" " [--profile NAME] [--verify]"
Type credentials into a login screen using compositor-specific profiles.
.TP
.BI boot\-sequence " SCRIPT"
Run a provisioning script with longer default timeouts.
.SS Calibration
.TP
.BI calibrate " [--grid NxN] [--output PATH] [--deploy METHOD] [--quick]"
Run click calibration grid to measure coordinate offset.
Default: 4x4 grid, clipboard deployment.
.SS Scripting & Recording
.TP
.BI run " SCRIPT"
Execute commands from a .rdpdo-script file.
Variables: {env:VAR}, {width}, {height}, {server}.
.TP
.BI play " PATH" " [SPEED]"
Replay a timed .rdpdo recording with optional speed multiplier.
.TP
.BI convert " INPUT" " OUTPUT"
Convert between recording (.rdpdo) and script (.rdpdo-script) formats.
Does not require an RDP connection.
.TP
.BI retry " COUNT"
Modifier: retry the next command up to COUNT times on failure.
Waits 500ms between attempts.
.TP
.B soft
Modifier: make the next command non-fatal. Logs failure but continues
the command chain. Combine with retry for resilient scripts.
.SS Baseline Management
.TP
.BI baseline " update NAME" " [--dir PATH]"
Save current screen as a named baseline reference.
.TP
.BI baseline " list" " [--dir PATH]"
List saved baselines.
.TP
.BI baseline " check NAME" " [TOLERANCE] [--dir PATH]"
Compare current screen against a saved baseline.
.SS Info & Diagnostics
.TP
.B info
Print connection info as JSON.
.TP
.B perf
Print performance metrics as JSON (FPS, latency, bandwidth).
.TP
.BI pause " SECONDS"
Pause for N seconds (supports fractions). Processes server PDUs during wait.
Aliases: sleep, wait.
.TP
.BI help " [COMMAND]"
Show help for all commands or a specific command.
Does not require an RDP connection.
.SH COORDINATE FORMATS
Positions can be specified as:
.TP
.B Pixels
500,300
.TP
.B Percentage
50%,50%
.TP
.B Named
center, top-left, top-right, bottom-left, bottom-right,
top-center, bottom-center, left-center, right-center
.SH TOLERANCE
Tolerance values accept either 0.0-1.0 or 1-100. Both 0.95 and 95
mean 95% match threshold.
.SH SCRIPT FORMAT
The .rdpdo-script format uses one command per line:
.PP
.RS
.nf
# Comments start with #
type "hello world"
key enter
pause 2
capture /tmp/screenshot.png
expect /tmp/expected.png 0.95 30

# Variables are expanded at parse time
type "{env:USERNAME}"
capture /tmp/{server}-{width}x{height}.png
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
All commands completed successfully.
.TP
.B 1
A command failed (timeout, assertion failure, connection error, etc.).
Soft failures do not affect the exit status.
.SH EXAMPLES
Simple login and screenshot:
.PP
.RS
rdpdo -s 192.168.1.10 -u admin -p secret type "password" key enter pause 3 capture /tmp/desktop.png
.RE
.PP
Visual testing with CI output:
.PP
.RS
rdpdo -s host --no-auth --json --junit results.xml \\
  mouse-hide expect /tmp/desktop.png 0.95 60 \\
  capture /tmp/actual.png
.RE
.PP
Resilient automation with retry and soft assertions:
.PP
.RS
rdpdo -s host --fail-capture /tmp/fails \\
  soft retry 3 expect /tmp/splash.png 0.9 10 \\
  type "admin" key tab type "password" key enter \\
  retry 5 waitfor /tmp/desktop.png 0.9 120 \\
  measure /tmp/app-icon.png --label app-ready
.RE
.PP
Measure login time:
.PP
.RS
rdpdo -s host -u user -p pass --json \\
  measure /tmp/desktop.png 0.9 120 --label login-time
.RE
.PP
Offline image comparison with exclusion zones:
.PP
.RS
rdpdo diff before.png after.png 0.99 \\
  --output diff.png --exclude 0,0,200x30
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B RDPDO_*
Environment variables referenced in scripts via {env:VARNAME}.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/rdpdo/calibration/
Calibration profiles (JSON), organized by server and resolution.
.TP
.I ~/.config/rdpdo/baselines/
Baseline screenshots for visual regression testing.
